      <description>&lt;p&gt;This post is a compact set of notes on the math and statistics foundations behind machine learning and deep learning, which I collected over the past few years.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 class=&#34;heading&#34; id=&#34;table-of-contents&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Table of Contents&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#table-of-contents&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://liuyiyueyue.github.io/llm/ml_fundamentals/#basic-terms&#34;&gt;Basic Terms&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://liuyiyueyue.github.io/llm/ml_fundamentals/#training-workflow&#34;&gt;Training Workflow&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://liuyiyueyue.github.io/llm/ml_fundamentals/#inference-workflow&#34;&gt;Inference Workflow&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://liuyiyueyue.github.io/llm/ml_fundamentals/#basic-ml-algorithms&#34;&gt;Basic ML Algorithms&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://liuyiyueyue.github.io/llm/ml_fundamentals/#chain-rule-backpropagation-and-forwardbackward-passes&#34;&gt;Chain Rule, Backpropagation, and Forward/Backward Passes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://liuyiyueyue.github.io/llm/ml_fundamentals/#evaluation-metrics&#34;&gt;Evaluation Metrics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://liuyiyueyue.github.io/llm/ml_fundamentals/#overfitting-and-regularization&#34;&gt;Overfitting and Regularization&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://liuyiyueyue.github.io/llm/ml_fundamentals/#bias-variance-and-cross-validation&#34;&gt;Bias, Variance, and Cross-Validation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://liuyiyueyue.github.io/llm/ml_fundamentals/#loss-and-optimization&#34;&gt;Loss and Optimization&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://liuyiyueyue.github.io/llm/ml_fundamentals/#activation-functions&#34;&gt;Activation Functions&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://liuyiyueyue.github.io/llm/ml_fundamentals/#normalization&#34;&gt;Normalization&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://liuyiyueyue.github.io/llm/ml_fundamentals/#probability-and-statistics-for-machine-learning&#34;&gt;Probability and Statistics for Machine Learning&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 class=&#34;heading&#34; id=&#34;basic-terms&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Basic Terms&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#basic-terms&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Machine learning usually starts with a model, a loss function, gradients, and an optimizer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
